olive oil
1 tin sweetcorn
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
½ bag coriander

• Drain the sweetcorn.
• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat! In a medium bowl, combine Louisiana spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add
chicken breast strips and turn to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken strips and corn until browned and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it is no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, combine slaw mix in a large bowl, along with half the mayonnaise and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.
• Microwave mini flourtortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.

• Bring everything to the table to serve.
• Build your tacos by topping tortillas with creamy slaw and Louisiana chicken strips and corn. Drizzle over remaining mayonnaise and tear over herbs (see
ingredients) to serve. Enjoy!